# proglang-keywords/c++.twlist
#
# language: C++ (C++98 through C++23 reserved keywords + standard library
# fundamentals + constants).
# source: ISO/IEC 14882 (C++ standard) — keyword list per [lex.key], plus
#   the fundamental types/identifiers (size_t, ptrdiff_t, etc., lowercased
#   without the `_t` suffix), the std namespace's stream + container
#   tokens that lex as single WORDs.
# notes: type prefix is literal `c++_` per developer spec. Standalone:
#   words shared with C (return, void, int, ...) get a parallel
#   c++_return tag — sortDict merges to a comma-joined singleton with
#   both c_return and c++_return, still zero-bit. `std::cout` is two
#   tokens after the `::` PUNCT split, so we list `cout`, `cin`, `cerr`
#   bare; the `std` prefix appears as its own `c++_std` entry.

# ----- C++ keywords (superset of C; including C++ additions) -----
c++_alignas        alignas
c++_alignof        alignof
c++_and            and
c++_asm            asm
c++_auto           auto
c++_bitand         bitand
c++_bitor          bitor
